Patagonia may be known for its alpine routes, but the granite blocs scattered around El Chaltén and Torres del Paine National Park have caught the eye of many intrepid climbers. For BD Athlete Nalle Hukkataival (@nalle_hukkataival), the allure of the boulders was enticing enough to dedicate a trip to Patagonia to sample and explore the blocs below the walls.

#liveclimbrepeat 

Video: @lena_bam

node.title: The Blocs Below the Walls: Nalle Hukkataival in Patagonia

— They’re strong, independent, fierce. They’re loyal and loving and, much like your belayer, always have your back. They’re crushers, dreamers, role models. We all have our best #beladies in our lives – the ones we can count on to be there, to inspire us, to push us. At Black Diamond, we’re constantly in awe of the number of bold, passionate women around us.
In honor of International Women's Day, tell us – who are your heroes? Use #beladies in your posts to be featured on our page. #internationalwomensday #liveclimbrepeat #liverunrepeat #liveskirepeat

node.text:
The timing was perfect: with the annual Kings and Queens of Corbet’s ready to take off, BD Athlete Parkin Costain (@parkincostain) set up shop for a week in Jackson Hole just as a classic Wyoming storm-cycle blanketed the hill with a few feet of fresh. With the unstable snowpack of the backcountry, Parkin decided to take advantage of the tram and go big on the 4,000-foot vertical runs that Jackson is famous for. You gotta get up to get down. 

#liveskirepeat
@blackdiamond_snow

Video by @benshicreative

node.title: Parkin Costain: Get Up to Get Down

"The pile of hardened gritstone blocks are scattered like a dump of washer-dryer combos at the base, and no number of big pads or the help of spotters can help you now. Elvis leg will be your death if you don’t attend to that little cobble, shiny and polished as a marble and half the size."

BD Ambassador @chris_schulte recently made a pilgrimage to explore “god’s own stone,” otherwise known as England’s famed and notorious gritstone. In his own words, everything you’ve heard about the “grit” is true … “except when it’s not.” 

Link in bio for more words by Schulte. #liveclimbrepeat

node.text:
In the fall of 2019, BD Athlete Joe Grant (@alpineworks) was invited to “The Land of Smiles” to experience first-hand the burgeoning Thai trail running community. This film and the accompanying essay by Joe (link in bio!), captures his lasting sentiment since leaving Thailand. As he puts it so eloquently, “the essential elements to a long and happy running life is the search for balance... While trail running is in its infancy in Thailand, they already have the right ingredients to be one step ahead.”

Link in bio for more.

#liverunrepeat

node.title: BD Athlete Joe Grant: This is Thailand

The Babsi Edition of our 9.2 Dry Climbing Rope is a true all-arounder that can handle any weather. Built for BD Athlete Babsi Zangerl (@babsizangerl) – a climber who sends it no matter whether she’s on the Nose of El Cap or run-out above a Z4 in the Dolomites – the the Babsi Edition 9.2 Dry is built for pushing limits on stone. 
 
Key Features:
– UIAA Dry: a dry-treated core and sheath keep this rope protected against weather from the inside out, and meets the UIAA Water Repellent standard
– 1x1 Woven Sheath provides more abrasion resistance
– Triple Dash Middle Marker adds margin of safety for identifying middle of rope
– Available in 60m, 70m and 80m lengths

Link in bio for more of the Babsi Collection.

node.text:
Located near @babsizangerl’s home in Bludenz, Austria, Lorüns is a sport climbing crag that’s home to decades’ old historical routes. Described as a “meeting point” for both the old and younger generations of the Austrian climbing community, Lorüns is close to Babsi’s heart. Her partner, Jacopo Larcher (@jacopolarcher), recently climbed a legendary 30-year-old project, in turn establishing the crag’s hardest route—Sprengstoff (9a), meaning “Explosive” in English.

Unfortunately, Lorüns is part of an area owned by a local quarry company and is under a constant and ever-increasing threat of destruction.

This past year, Babsi committed herself to making Sprengstoff’s second ascent, in part to push her climbing, but also to use her ascent to drive awareness to the crag’s impending threat. Follow Babsi as she commits to the fight of Sprengstoff.
